#HELPS

0 Classes~
There are 13 available classes.  For more information on an individual class,
refer to the help file (help dragon, help drow, etc.).  If you need to know
anything not listed in these files, ask an experienced player or an immortal.
To become classed, simply type autoclass once you meet the stat requirements.

#rAngel#n       - Divine warriors of righteousness and light.
Demon       - Infernal lords of chaos and shadow.
Dragon      - Mythical beasts who soar through the sky.
#PDrow#n         - Cruel masters of the underdark.
#cElementalist#n - Instinctive users of natural magics.
#RFae#n          - Ethereal beings of pure elemental force.
#CHighlander#n   - Immortal blademasters...of death! (*gasp*)
#pMage#n         - WoD mages, spheres, paradox, and all.
#7Monk#n         - Devout practioners of unarmed combat.
#0Ninja#n        - Shadowy assassins wielding poisoned blades.
#LSorcerer#n     - Wielders of the very fabric of reality.
#rVampire#n      - Undead denizens of the night.
#oWerewolf#n     - Shapeshifting servants of Gaia.

Related Helps: Reqs, Clans, Leaders, and 'help <class name>'.
~

0 Reqs Requirements~
After you get the reqs listed here, type autoclass to class.

Dragon:       4 Str, 1 Dex, 3 Con, 2 Int, 2 Wis
#PDrow#n:         2 Str, 4 Dex, 1 Con, 3 Int, 2 Wis
#cElementalist#n: 2 Str, 1 Dex, 2 Con, 3 Int, 4 Wis
#CHighlander#n:   4 Str, 2 Dex, 3 Con, 1 Int, 2 Wis
#LSorcerer#n:     2 Str, 2 Dex, 1 Con, 4 Int, 3 Wis
#7Monk#n:         2 Str, 3 Dex, 2 Con, 1 Int, 4 Wis
#0Ninja#n:        3 Str, 4 Dex, 2 Con, 2 Int, 1 Wis
#rVampire#n:      3 Str, 2 Dex, 4 Con, 2 Int, 1 Wis
#oWerewolf#n:     4 Str, 2 Dex, 3 Con, 1 Int, 2 Wis
#pMage#n:         1 Str, 2 Dex, 2 Con, 4 Int, 3 Wis

Related Helps: Class, and 'help <class name>'.
~

