0 Challenge~
To challenge one of the leaders of a class you must be of that class, not
already a leader, and have at least 5 status during the challenge.  All
challenges should be posted in such a way that the person being challenged,
and all imms can see the note.  Yes you have to write a note to challenge.
When challenged, the leader has a week to respond before they forfeit their
position.  The challenge will take place when both the challenger and
challenged are online as well as an imm(Akuma) to supervise.  The person
challenged sets the winning condition as tie, destroy, or decap.  Both
players are expected to not be under the effects of any other classes powers,
such as a Sorcerer's bless, or a Monk's almighty favor.  Any other,
more exotic qualifications must be agreed by both players involved.  Refer
any questions you may have to Akuma.

Related Helps: Leaders, and Clan.
~

0 Angel~
Angels are divine beings of grace and holy power. Custodians of righteousness
and light, angels possess unparalleled knowledge of the heavens. They wield
sacred powers granted by the divine, allowing them to protect the innocent and
smite evil. Angels begin their existence as mortals who have been embraced by
the Archangel, the supreme leader of all angels.

Angel Abilities
 Pact         - Angels may form pacts with mortal champions.
 Inpart       - Angels can bestow divine powers upon their champions.
 Divine Forms - Angels can transform into Angelform or take Cherub form.
 Champion Aid - Angels grant boons to their chosen champions: Fangs, Claws,
                Wings, Nightsight, Might, Toughness, Speed, Travel, Scry,
                Shadowsight, Aura, and many more.
 Inferno      - Angels can call down divine flames to smite their enemies.
 Holy Channel - Angels use the Communion channel to communicate.

Related Helps: Class, Inpart, and Leaders.
~

0 Dragons~
The fierce and lethal dracos.  Strong and proud reptilian creatures, their mere
presence can induce fear into the brave hearts of many. Breathtaking to behold,
glorious in the kill, be they good or evil, impressive to the highest extreme.
As with most creatures, they are split between good - the metallic dragons, and
evil - the chromatic.  Capable of growing up to sixty feet, these monstrous
beings stand high on the hierarchy of power.  Growing stronger as their age
grows, they can become one of the strongest beings to ever tread the earth.

Dragon Abilities
 Age       - Dragons gain power and strength as they grow older.
 Powers    - As they age, Dragons can gain access to a variety of powers.
 Types     - Dragons come in a variety of types, each with its own breath weapon.
 Morph     - Dragons can shift into and out of Human form at will.
 Telepathy - Dragons are able to communicate with each other through telepathy.

Related Helps: Dragonskills, and Class.
~

0 Dragonskills~
Dragons grow older through the use of the 'dragonskills' command.  As they
grow older, they become able to purchase other abilities through the
'dragonskills' command, as listed below.  Dragon abilities cost 1000 DP per
required age tier beyond Hatchling.

Age           DP Cost  QP Cost  MR  Abilities
---           -------  -------  --  ---------
Hatchling     Starting Age      0   None
Very Young    2500     0        0   Fangs <fangs>, Nightsight <nightsight>
Young         5000     0        0   Horns <horns>, Claws <claws>
Juvenile      7500     0        0   Wings <wings>, Breath <breath>
Young Adult   10000    0        0   Tail <tail>
Adult         15000    500      0   Truesight <heighten>
Mature Adult  25000    1000     10  Dust <dust>
Old           35000    1500     20  Scry <scry>, Magic (lowers casting time)
Very Old      50000    2000     30  Readaura <readaura>
Ancient       70000    2500     40  Shield <shield>
Wyrm          100000   3000     50  None
Ancient Wyrm  Leader Position   50  None

Related Helps: Dragon.
~


0 Drow~
The Drow are perhaps known to be the most merciless, and dangerous race 
known beneath the surface. They are a subrace of the Elven race, with 
ebony black skin, though the rest of their features, shapes, and hair 
colors range in variance as humans do.

Drow Powers
  Prayer - Drow power system.  Uses DP.
  Dimensional Door - Inherent travel power.
  Sign - Drow channel.
  Drowarmor - Costs 8000 dp & 400 qp. Grants 10% MR each.
    Cloak - Fireshield.
    Helmet - Sanctuary.
    Breastplate - Regeneration.
    Bracer - Haste.
  Meditate - Drow have enhanced healing while meditating.
  Drowupkeep - Displays known and active powers.

Related Helps: Prayer, and Class.
~

0 Prayer~
Skip disc         (fly)         {syntax: skipdisc}      DP cost: 5000
Spider eyes       (scry)        {syntax: scry}          DP cost: 7500
Acid bolt         (aggy attack) {syntax: acidbolt}      DP cost: 5000
Attunement        (loyal)       {syntax: attunement}    DP cost: 1000
Spider bite       (poison bite) {automatic}             DP cost: 7500
Venom immunity                  {automatic}             DP cost: 5000
Summon spider                   {syntax: summonspider}  DP cost: 8000
Lloth's web       (web spell)   {syntax: web}           DP cost: 8000
Speed             (4 levels)    {automatic}             DP cost: 10000 each
Toughness                       {automatic}             DP cost: 8000
Might                           {automatic}             DP cost: 8000
Blindfight                      {automatic}             DP cost: 5000
Globe of Darkness               {syntax: globedarkness} DP cost: 9500
Faerie fire                     {syntax: faeriefire}    DP cost: 5000
Dual Wield        (two weapons) {automatic}             DP cost: 10000
Read aura                       {syntax: readaura}      DP cost: 6000
Darkvision        (nightsight)  {syntax: darkvision}    DP cost: 5000
Heighten                        {syntax: heighten}      DP cost: 20000

Related Helps: Drow.
~

0 Demon~
Demons are infernal beings of immense power and ambition. Born from the depths
of chaos and shadow, demons are driven by a hunger for dominion and corruption.
They serve the Demon Lord, the supreme ruler of all demons, and together they
plot to expand their dark influence across the realms. Mortals may be embraced
as demons through a dark pact with the Demon Lord.

Demon Abilities
 Pact         - Demons may form pacts with mortal champions.
 Inpart       - Demons can bestow infernal powers upon their champions.
 Demonic Forms- Demons can transform into Demonform or summon Imp servants.
 Champion Aid - Demons grant boons to their chosen champions: Fangs, Claws,
                Hooves, Nightsight, Might, Toughness, Speed, Travel, Scry,
                Shadowsight, and many more.
 Inferno      - Demons can rain infernal flames upon their enemies.
 Dark Channel - Demons use the Communion channel to communicate.
 Vision       - Demons can increase their magical vision and power.

Related Helps: Class, Inpart, and Leaders.
~

0 Elementalists~
Called everything from geomancers to wizards, these men and women have devoted 
their lives in learning how to channel the raw energy of the universe and 
forming it into various things from falling rain to the hottest fire.

Elementalists can access all elements, but they specialize in only ONE element. 
As a result, their ability in the opposing element is weakened. You must have
all your elements at 8 in order to specialize, but you may switch out of the
specialization with the Elemskill command.

Elementalist Elements:
 Fire        - Element of Strength and Ferocity
 Water       - Element of Order and Conformity
 Wind        - Element of Chaos and Speed
 Earth       - Element of Toughness
 Sun         - Element of Light and Protection
 Moon        - Element of Darkness and Illusion
 Time        - Element of Travel and Moments
 Infinity    - Element of Unity and the Void

Elementalist Commands:
 elemskill   - Displays and improves your Elements.
 upkeep      - Displays what abilities are currently active.
 elemarmor   - Creates class relics.  Costs 400qp and 100 primal.
 spiritspeak - The Elementalist channel

Related Helps: Elements, Elements2, and Class.
~

0 Elements~
Fire - Element of Strength and Ferocity.
1 : Flare Arrow    - Launches flaming arrows.
5 : Flame Aura     - Strength increase. <auto>
8 : Fire Blade     - Ignites your weapons.
10: Phoenix Form   - Turn into a Phoenix.

Water - Element of Order and Conformity.
1 : Icicle Storm  - Conjures a barrage of icicles.
5 : Aqua Barrier  - Surrounds you with a barrier of water.
8 : Water Travel  - Allows quick travel.
10: Water Control - Stuns opponents.

Earth - Element of Toughness.
1 : Local Quake   - Shakes the earth.
5 : Earthen Skin  - Defense increase. <auto>
8 : Stone Blast   - Blasts everything.
10: Liquify Stone - Turns the land into quicksand.

Wind - Element of Chaos and Speed.
1 : Wind Wings     - Lifts you into the air.
5 : Wind Song      - Speed increase. <auto>
8 : Wind Blades    - Slashes with blades of wind.
10: Atoning Winds  - Slows opponents.

Related Helps: Elementalist, and Elements2
~

0 Elements2~
Sun - Element of Light and Protection.
1 : Sun Bath        - Showers target with healing light.
5 : Holy Aura       - Surrounds you with a holy aura.
8 : Solar Flash     - Blinds opponents.
10: Solar Light     - Grants you a halo of sunlight.
	
Moon - Element of Darkness and Illusion.
1 : Mirage Slice   - Summons an illusionary double to attack.
5 : Mirage Bodies  - Evade increase. <auto>
8 : Night Blade    - Life stealing double attack.
10: Spiral Moon    - Weakens with dark energy.

Time - Element of Travel and Moments.
1 : Speed Vision   - Attack increase. <auto>
5 : Hasten         - Speed increase. <auto>
8 : Quick Chant    - Spell speed increase. <auto>
10: Slow           - Slows target.

Infinity - Element of Unity and the Void.
1 : Far Sight      - Watches from afar.
3 : Cloak of Sight - Hides you at a distance.
5 : Infinite Sight - Opens your eyes to everything.
8 : Focus          - Skill increase. <auto>
10: Ultima Wave    - Creates a wave of destruction.

Related Helps: Elementalist, and Elements.
~

0 Fae~
The Fae are ethereal beings of pure elemental force, existing at the boundaries
between the mortal and spirit worlds. These magnificent creatures harness the
raw power of nature itself, growing stronger through their command of elemental
energies. With delicate wings and an alien grace, Fae are both beautiful and
terrifying in their power. They channel through Windwhisper and draw strength
from the very elements that surround them.

Fae Abilities
 Elemental Force - Fae can increase their Elemental Attack and Defence.
 Earthshield     - Grants damage resistance (2% per Defence point plus 10%).
 True Form       - Fae can assume their true form when needed.
 Bloodpact       - At maximum power, Fae can form mystical blood pacts.
 Faestorm        - Fae can summon devastating elemental storms.
 Wing Slice      - Fae can strike with razor-sharp wing attacks.
 Soar            - Fae can take flight through the air.
 Wail            - Fae can emit a powerful piercing wail.
 Natural Magic   - Fae have access to Scry and Read Aura abilities.
 Channel         - Fae use Windwhisper to communicate.

Related Helps: Class, and Elementalists.
~

0 Highlanders~
For as long as history itself, there have been the immortals. Those, whom 
through one reason or another are unable to die through normal means.  They 
wander, be they good or evil, destined to forever uphold their beliefs through 
adversity, and to, through beheading, rid the world of their adversaries, and 
each other.  Practiced with their chosen weapons, they are the weapon masters.

* Increase - Increases HL abilities. <Increase (ability)>
* Forge    - Makes a hasting katana. <forge>
           - Reforges a weapon into a katana. <forge (weapon)>
* Where    - Highlanders can make better use of the where command to track
              people they can't see.

Related Helps: Highabil, and Class.
~

0 Highabil~
Weaponry  - Damage bonuses...
Attack    - Break, Damcap, and Speed bonuses.
Defense   - Avoid, Soak, and Magic Resist bonuses.
Abilities - Allows use of class abilities as follows.
 1. Heighten    - Improves vision. <heighten>
 2. Blade Flash - Removes target's sight, causing induced blindness. <bflash>
 3. Bash        - Damages target, causing them to recover before moving again. <bash>
 4. Twist       - Temporary speed increase, allowing one to parry more often. <htwist>
 5. Judgement   - Though not supernatural, highlanders are a fair judge of strength. <judgement>
 6. Lunge       - Opening attack that leaves your opponent unbalanced. <lunge>

Related Helps: Highlanders.
~


0 Mages~
True WoD Mages.  They bend reality to their will, but as the result of a world
of non-believers the world bends back.  Mages cast powerful spells which are
divided into spheres, but gain paradox which strikes back at them as they cast
their more powerful spells.

Mage's power is based on their Arete. The syntax to increase your arete is 'Arete'.

The nine spheres of mage spells are:
Correspondence, Entropy, Forces, Life, Mind, Spirit, Prime, Matter, and Time.

To see the powers you have available type 'powers'.
To see what you are currently affected by type 'upkeep'.

Mages can create class equipment using 'magearmor'. This equipment costs 100 primal
 and 400 qps.

Related Helps: Spheres, Quintessence, Backlash, Mageclans, 'help <sphere name>
 and Class.
~

0 Mageclans~
#pAkashic Brotherhood:#n Simplistic martial artists.#p Focus: Mind
#pCelestial Chorus:#n Wielders of divine magic. #pFocus: Prime
#pCult of Esctasy:#n A free will group who strives to reach beyond their normal limitations. #pFocus: Time#n
#pDreamspeakers:#n A group with deep connections to the land and their native ways. #pFocus: Spirit#n
#pEuthanatos:#n Death is not THE end, it is AN end. All things cycle. #pFocus: Entropy#n
#pOrder of Hermes:#n A complex organization that seeks perfection. #pFocus: Forces#n
#pSons of Ether:#n Tinkers who create things that simply shouldn't be possible. #pFocus: Matter#n
#pVerbena:#n Life is the greatest mystery of the universe. All life is a cycle. #pFocus: Life#n
#pVirtual Adepts:#n Information is the ultimate power and the ultimate tool. #pFocus: Correspondence#n
#pHollow Ones:#n <Akuma's Edit>Stupid Goth posers</Akuma's Edit>. #pFocus: None#n

Related Helps: Clan, and Mage.
~

0 Spheres~
[CORRESPONDENCE] Understanding of Space and Relationships with it.
[   ENTROPY    ] Mastery of Luck, Fate, and Chaos.
[    FORCES    ] Command over the Natural elements, from fire to physics.
[     LIFE     ] Insight into the makeup of living things.
[    MATTER    ] A grasp of non-living structures--And how they can be changed.
[     MIND     ] An insight to the inner workings of the mind.
[    PRIME     ] Command over Quintessence, The cornerstone of the universe.
[    SPIRIT    ] Insight into the spiritual World.
[     TIME     ] Mastery of Time and Avoiding its affects.

[*] 'Sphere' will show you the spheres you have learned.
    'Sphere learn (sphere)' Allows you to increase your knowledge of a sphere.
     Sphere's cost 20 primal * the level you wish to learn.

Related Helps: Mage, and 'help <sphere name>sphere'(ie. help timesphere).
~

0 Quintessence~
Quintessence is the fundamental building block of the universe. As mages increase
their power (Arete) they become able to store more quintessence in their bodies.
This quintessence can be used to power almost any of their spells to an even
greater than normal result.

Related Helps: Mage, and Backlash.
~

0 Backlash~
Whenever a mage casts a spell the will of the world works against it. When casting
minor spells this has almost no effect, but with powerful spells it can be quite
devastating. Depending on the conditions and power of the spell, mages build up
paradox. Once they have built up enough paradox, or gain enough from a single spell,
it causes a backlash. In a backlash the forces of paradox the mage has been
accumulating release all at once, dealing potentially devastating damage.

Related Helps: Mage, and Quintessence.
~

0 Correspondencesphere~
Level 1: Allows spells to target the caster.
Level 2: Allows spells to target others in the same room.
Level 4: Rift: A travel power which creates a portal that has a duration based on the amount of quintessence used.
	Syntax: rift (target) (quintessence)
Level 5: Allows spells to target others in the same area.

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Entropysphere~
Level 1: Detect Weakness: Break/Damcap bonuses (auto)
Level 2: Beginner's Luck: Allows the caster to hit automaticly the first attacks in the next combat.
	Syntax: beginnersluck (quintessence)
Level 4: Brittle Bones: Cuts through the opponents soak for a number of attacks.
	Syntax: brittlebones (target) (quintessence)
Level 5: Mutate Ephemera: Paralyzes the opponent, and twists fate to send their attacks back against them.
	Syntax: mutateephemera (target) (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Forcessphere~
Level 1: Nightsight: Gives nightsight
	Syntax: nightsight
Level 2: Electrical Chaos: One target damage spell.
	Syntax: electricalchaos (target) (quintessence)
Level 4: Friction Curse: Slows down an opponent and converts their movement into damage.
	Syntax: frictioncurse (target) (quintessence)
Level 5: Inferno: Area affect damage spell that causes flames.
	Syntax: inferno (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Lifesphere~
Level 1: Readaura
	Syntax: readaura (target)
Level 2: Sorc Heal: A one target healing spell.
	Syntax: sorcheal (target) (quintessence)
Level 4: Better Body: Increases one person's ability to fight.
	Syntax: sorcbetterbody (target) (str/dex/con/int/wis) (quintessence)
Level 5: Polymorph Other: Polymorph's the target into a pig, removing the benefits from any form they were in.
	Syntax: polymorphother (target) (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Mattersphere~
Level 1: Analyze: Identify
	Syntax: analyze (target)
Level 2: Shatter Wall: Destroys walls.
	Syntax: shatterwall (direction)
Level 4: Scuplture: Creates walls.
	Syntax: sculpture (direction)
Level 5: Alter Weight: Increases the gravity around your target, crushing them, and then slowing their actions.
	Syntax: sorcalterweight (target) (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Mindsphere~
Level 1: Heighten
	Syntax: heighten
Level 2: Scry
	Syntax: scry (target)
Level 4: Shield: Prevents scry from working on you. (Mages do no regenerate with shield activated)
	Syntax shield
Level 5: Invis: Blocks your images from other's minds.
	Syntax: sorcinvis (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Primesphere~
Level 1: Heart's Blood: Allows you to take damage in order to put more quintessence into a spell than you have.
	Syntax: heartsblood
Level 2: Holy Smote: Creates a sword of quintessence that fights for you.
	Syntax: holysmote
Level 4: Enchant Weapon: Channels quintessence into a weapon making it cause aggrivated damage.
	Syntax: sorcenchant (target)
Level 5: Paradox Ward: Prevents against the damage from a paradox backlash.
	Syntax: ward (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Spiritsphere~
Level 1: Spirit Sense: Allows you to see into the umbra.
	Syntax: spiritsence
Level 2: Spirit Caress: Allows you to reach into the umbra and make one attack.
	Syntax: spiritcaress
Level 4: Step Sideways: Allows you to enter and leave the umbra.
	Syntax: stepsideways (quintessence)
Level 5: Break Dreamshell: Allows you to enter and leave the deep umbra.
	Syntax: breakdreamshell (quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~

0 Timesphere~
Level 1: Time Sense: Lowers Speed (auto)
Level 2: Future Sense: Raises Avoid (auto)
Level 4: Contingency: Prepares a spell to be cast when you enter combat.
	contingency (spell)
Level 5: Doublecast: Allows you to cast another mage spell twice.
	doublecast (the spell exactly as you would cast it normally, including targets and quintessence)

Related Helps: Mages, and Spheres.
~


0 Monks~
Monks are a breed of holy warriors well known for their training.  They have
mastered the use of their body in combat over mere weapons.  By harnessing the
divine powers of the realm in conjunction with their elite fighting skills, Monks
are a force to be reckoned with.

Commands:
Monk      - The monk channel.
Monklearn - Command to improve powers.
Decide    - Inducts a clanless monk into your clan. (Priest/Abbot only)
Expel     - Casts a monk in your clan out. (Abbot only)
Monkarmor - Creates monk only relic armor.
Mclan     - Displays the stats of monks in your clan.

Related Helps: Monklearn, and Class
~

0 Monklearn Arts Techs Mantras~
Mantras - A myriad of non-combat abilities.
1: Eyes of God      - Increases awareness. (heighten)
2: Trio Mantra      - Grants knowledge. (scry/readaura/shield)
3: Rejuvenation     - Gives regeneration. (auto)
4: Healing Touch    - Allows you to heal with a touch. (touch)
5: Almighty Favor   - Grants a blessing. (almighty/almighty group)
6: Spirit Guardian  - Summons a guardian. (spiritguardian)
7: Celestial Path   - Instantaneous travel. (celestial)
8: Cloak of Life    - Saves you from death. (lifecloak)

Arts - Combat abilities and styles.
1: Focus of Mind    - Boosts damage. (auto)
2: Reinforce        - Boosts accuracy. (auto)
3: Speed of Wind    - Boosts speed. (auto)
4: Illusionary Form - Boosts avoid. (auto)
5: Heart of Oak     - Strengthens the body. (auto)
6: Adamantium Hands - Hardens your fists. (auto)
7: Mystic Soul      - Boosts damage. (auto)
8: Dragon Movement  - Grants Wavefist attack. (auto)

Techs - Fighting techniques and powers.
1: Repeating Fist  - Multihit technique. (repeat)
2: Aura Shot       - Life stealing attack. (aura)
3: Blitz           - Area affect damage. (blitz)
4: Invite Beast    - Possesses weak creatures. (invite)
5: Crippling Kick  - Mana burning kick. (cripple)
6: Dark Blaze      - Blinds your foes. (darkblaze)
7: Stun Fist       - Damaging stun attack. (stun)
8: Chimera Form    - Powerful form. (chimera)

Related Helps: Monk.
~


0 Ninja~
Ninja are masters of the night and darkness. Though mortal, they have their own
unique ways of surviving in the world of vampires and werewolves. Each ninja
studies under three principles of life, Sora, Chikyu, and Ningenno. Mastery of
these principles account for the stealth and strength of the ninja.

Powers:
  Ki         - Source of ninja power.
  Principles - The main source of a ninja's power. <principle (prin) improve>
    Sora     - Gives non-combat skills. 
    Chikyu   - Gives combat preparation skills.
    Ningenno - Gives combat skills.
  Ninjaarmor - Purchases ninja class eq.
  Mikt       - Ninja only channel.

Related Helps: Principles, and Class.
~

0 Principles Sora Chikyu Ningenno~
Sora - *Heaven*.  Each level adds 25 to max Michi.
1 : Michi       - Improves combat abilities. (michi) <100 ki> (calm)
4 : Kanzuite    - Raises your awareness. (heighten/readaura/scry)
6 : Kakusu      - Cloaks you in shadows. (kakusu) <20 ki, movement drains>
8 : Bomuzite    - Renders opponents unconcious. (bomuzite) <20 ki>
10: Mizotamouyo - Allows quick transportation to distant places. (mizotamouyo)

Chikyu - *Earth*.  Each level adds damage/avoid.
1 : Mienaku     - "Ninja VANISH!" - TMNT. (mienaku) <20 ki>
4 : Orimasu     - Increased focus improves healing rates. (orimasu) <50 ki>
6 : Gunaya      - Entangles your opponent in sticky strands of webbing. (web) <10 ki>
8 : Tsumazuku   - Leaves opponents unable to respond to your attack. (tsumazuku)
10: HaraKiri    - Increases power through pain. (harakiri)

Ningenno - *Humanity*.  Each level adds speed/break.
1 : Tsume       - Attaches steel-bladed claws to your wrist. (tsume)
4 : Shuurai     - Lightning quick piercing attacks. (shuurai)
6 : Shuriken    - Throws small blades during combat. (automatic)
8 : Tsuin Ittou - Allows the use of two weapons. (automatic)
10: Hakunetsu   - Delivers a powerful piercing attack to your opponents vitals. (hakunetsu)

Related Helps: Ninja.
~


0 Sorcerers~
Sorcerers are wielders of natural, instinctive magics.  They are born to magic
rather than taught at a later age, and they enjoy complete flexibility with
their spells.  In addition to being able to write their own spells, Sorcerers
have a few extra "basic" spells, and can cast spells faster than normal as
their colors improve.
** This is a "Book Mage" type class, but it is heavily modified.  Do NOT
    expect standard Mage Primer spells to work.  Refer to these helpfiles
    for current mechanics.

Commands:
Colors     - Trains a color.
Write      - Writes a spell onto a page.
Chant      - Chants a spell out of a book.
Sorccreate - Creates the necessary book writing items.
Enchant    - Enchants a weapon or armor.
Vision     - Improves sight.
Sorctalk   - Sorcerer only channel.

Spells: (Syntax: c '<spell>' unless specified otherwise)
Charm Person  - Allows a mobile to be ordered.
Transport     - Sends an item to another person.
Insert Page   - Inserts a page into a book.
Remove Page   - Removes a page from a book.
Find Familiar - Summons an animal for you to command(use [ to give commands).

Umbra         - Moves you into the Umbral plane. <Not in.  Use the Umbra command>
Ethereal      - Makes you ethereal. <Not in.  Use an affect spell>

Related Helps: Chants, Writing, and Class.
~

0 Chants~
Most of a Sorcerer's power comes from the ability to create and use his own
spells.  Writing spells can be a difficult thing for a new sorcerer to learn,
understand and master, but hopefully this helpfile and the following ones will
help all the new sorcerers learn to make basic spells, and understand whats
going on when they write certain things.  Mastery of writing these books,
however, can only come through experience.  Note that Sorcerer is a complicated
class and these help files are on the long side.  However, you need to read ALL
of them before you can really start writing your spells, because one helpfile
can't possibly contain all the information your need to write.

Starting with a few basic commands:
Sorccreate    - Creates objects used in book writing.
       Syntax : sorccreate (book/page/pen)
write         - Writes important stuff on books and pages.
       Syntax : write (page/book) (line/title)
insert/remove - Inserts or removes a page from a book.
       Syntax : c 'insert page' page book (*) c 'remove page' book
chant         - Actually casts a spell which has been written on a page and 
                 inserted into a book.  The book to be chanted must be held.
       Syntax : chant <target>

Related Helps: Writing, Damage spells, Affect Spells, Action Spells, and Sorcerer.
~

0 Writing~
Writing a book is basically a formula in which you plug in the spell you want
to write.  Before using this, you'll want a pen and a book in your inventory,
both of which you can obtain by reading help chant.  The basic layout for
writing a page follows:

sorccreate page              // Creates your page
wear pen                     // Wears the pen so you can write with it
write page title <blah>      // Titles the page for easy reference
write page line <blah>       // Writes a line to the page, repeated MANY times
c 'insert page' page book    // Puts the page into a book, ready to be used

Titles can be anything you want, they are only used for reference.  Lines on
the other hand must be very specific or the spell will fail.  Basic lines
follow, the more specific ones for each spell type can be found in help
damage, affect, and action.

start.<type>.spell           // Starts a spell, type can be damage, affect, or
                             // action
message.1: <message>         // First message - use defined by spell type
message.2: <message>         // Second message - use defined by spell type
message.3: <message>         // Third message - use defined by spell type
next.page                    // Tells the spell to use the next page too
end.<color>                  // Ends the spell and defines its color, color
                             // can be any magic color listed in the Sorcerer
                             // colors command, also end.random will use a
                             // different color every time the page gets
                             // chanted

In all spells, start.<type>.spell, and end.<color> are necessary.  All spells
also require message.1-.3.  Next.page can be used to chain up to 10 pages
together for lethal effects.

Related Helps: Chant, Damage Spells, Affect Spells, Action Spells, and Sorcerer.
~

0 'Damage spells'~
Damage spells are the meat and drink of both PKing and exping.  They give
Sorcerers the ability to lay down the hurt, and lay it down good.  Damage
spells may only be used on people in the same room as you.  When writing a
damage spell, there are are no extra lines required.  Each color, however,
has a different end result.

Purple - Deals damage to all mobs and pks not in your group.
 Damage: 100 - 140 * Purple.  Mana: 800.
Red    - Deals damage to one target.
 Damage: 140 - 180 * Red.     Mana: 600.
Blue   - Heals damage from one target.
 Heals:  100 - 140 * Blue.    Mana: 400.
Green  - Heals damage on self only.
 Heals:   80 - 120 * Green.   Mana: 500.
Yellow - Deals damage to one target.
 Damage:  40 - 200 * Yellow.  Mana: 200.
Black  - Deals damage and aggravated damage to one target.
 Damage:  80 - 120 * Black.   Mana: 700.

Damage spells are easy to write.  Start the spell, specify the three
messages (message.1 is the strike message, message.2 is shown to you, and
message.3 is shown to the room), tag a next.page if you want, then end it
in the color you want to get the desired effect.

Damage spells also have a carry over affect.  The color of the previous
page in a chain will give a bonus or change the usage of the current page.

Color + Same color = Dam + (10 * color)
Purple - Makes the spell affect an area.
        Combined with green will heal only your group.
Red    - +(20 * red) to damage or heal.
Blue   - Turns damages to heals, +(30 * blue) to heals
Green  - Autotargets heals on self and damage on who you are fighting.
        Combined with purple will only hit mobs.
Yellow - -200 mana, +(random(-10, 10) * yellow) damage.
Black  - Adds aggravated.  Mixed with healing will heal aggravated.
        -(20 * black) damage/heal.

Related Helps: Chant, Writing, Affect Spells, Action Spells, and Sorcerer.
~

0 'Affect spells'~
Affect spells allow sorcerers to manipulate the stats of both themselves
and their enemies.  Proper application of affect spells in a chain can
make damage spells much more effective.  Affects are usable on anyone in
the same area as you(use where).  In writing an affect spell, there are
several more lines which can and must be utilized.

affect: <affect bit>         // What affects to set, list below
apply: <apply bit>           // What stat to effect, list below
duration: <0-50>             // Duration in number of ticks of spell
reversed                     // Penalizes listed stats

Affect allows you set specific affects such as Web, Flaming, and Sanct on
your target.  Apply can be used to give bonuses to your stats to improve
your abilities, and when combined with a reverse can hinder your foes.
Message.1 displays to self, message.2 displays to the target, message.3
displays to the room.  An example of a blessing page follows.

start.affect.spell             // Starts the spell
apply: hp                      // Applies the bonus to hp...
apply: mana                    // And applies it to mana
duration: 50                   // Sets the duration to max
message.1: You ##lbless##n $N.   // Displayed to caster(you)
message.2: $n ##lblesses##n you. // Displayed to target
message.3: $n ##lblesses##n $N.  // Displayed to room
next.page                      // Moves on to the next page
end.blue                       // Ends the spell, colors the affect blue

This page would give you a bonus to you hp and mana for 50 ticks.  Now,
it's time for a list of what affects and applies you can put out there.
The stuff in parenthesis are how much of a boost it gives, based on the
bonus.

Apply:
hp   (color * 250)  damroll (color * 10)  armor (color * 10)
mana (color * 250)  hitroll (color * 10)  save  (color * 1)
Affect:
blind        umbra        sanct        faerie.fire  curse
flaming      poison       ethereal     sleep        web

Related Helps: Chant, Writing, Damage Spells, Action Spells, and Sorcerer.
~

0 'Action spells'~
Used for summoning, traveling, readaura and scry.

Simple helpfile:
Purple = Object Summon    Yellow = Object Travel
Red    = Summoning        Blue   = Traveling
Green  = Readaura         Black  = Scry

All action spells are global.  Unaffected by ranks in colored magic.  Object
summon spells make the object summoned unusable in quests.  Mobile summon spells
set the mob to give no exp on death.

Messages:
Purple/Yellow: 1 = To You.  2 = To character's room.  3 = To object's room.
Red: 1 = To Victim.  2 = To victim's room.  3 = To you AND your room.
Blue: 1 = To You.  2 = To start room.  3 = To target room.
Green/Black: 1 = To victim.  2 = To you.  3 = To your room.

Related Helps: Chant, Writing, Damage Spells, Affect Spells, and Sorcerer.
~


0 Werewolf~
At the beginning of things, Gaia - the world and the spirit that embodies it - 
set all things in a balance that would maintain and encourage life.  Near the 
top of this chain of being was humanity, and above them were the Garou - the 
sacred warriors of the spirit.  They were appointed to be the crusaders 
against the Wyrm, who spreads its cancer through the humans.  They are the 
preservers of the raw essence of life, of nature's diversity and purity.  They 
are the Earth's immune system, fighting the disease of the Wyrm.  They are the 
werewolves, and they fight and destroy the children of the Wyrm (such as the 
vampires) at every opportunity.

Garou Commands
 Howl      - A special channel that only werewolves can understand.
 Advance   - Raises Garou ranks.
 Gnosis    - Raises your permanent Gnosis.  Used to power gifts.  Opposite of
            Rage.  Represents a Wolf's spiritual energies.
 Rage      - Raises your permanent Rage.  Used to power gifts.  Opposite of
            Gnosis.  Represents a Wolf's primal Beast.
 Shift     - Allows you to change your form.
 Tribegift - Selects your chosen gifts.  These gifts raise to 5 instead of 3.
 Wwarmor   - Wolf EQ each piece costs 400 qps, 100 primal.
 Wwgifts   - Shows a list of all the gifts you have available.
 Wwpowers  - Lists all the commands (NOT powers) available to you.
 Wwupkeep  - Lists all active powers.

Related Helps: Class, Ranks, Shift, Breeds, Auspices, and Tribes.
~

0 Shift~
Werewolves naturally have the ability to shift from man to wolf, and anywhere
in between.  Each form has its own advantages and disadvantages.  In addition
to the listed statistical differences, certain gifts can only be used in some
of the forms.

Homid  - Human.  No effect.
Glabro - Near-Human.  +200 damcap, +100 soak.
Crinos - Wolf-man.  +400 damcap, +1 speed, +150 soak.
Hispo  - Near-Wolf.  +300 damcap, +2 speed, +150 soak.
Lupus  - Wolf.  +200 damcap, +2 speed, +100 soak.

Related Helps: Werewolf, and Breeds.
~

0 Ranks~
Garou can advance through 5 ranks.  Garou start at rank 1, and through the 
advance command can raise themselves to rank 4.  Rank 5 is a Leadership type
position, and requires a Challenge(help challenge) to attain.  The ranks are,
in order, Cliath, Fostern, Adren, Athro, and Elder.  Ranks 1 through 4 all
give a myriad of small bonuses to help you in combat.

In order to attain to each rank, you must have a Gnosis and Rage of 50 +
(10 * current rank) and (500 * current rank) mobkills.

Related Helps: Werewolf.
~

