0 Vampires~
Vampires are the creatures of the night and thus take damage if exposed 
to daylight.  Vampires cannot eat food, or drink any liquids except for 
blood.  If they cannot drink blood for a long duration of time they will 
start taking damage or maybe even go berserk, so it's a good idea to feed 
from time to time.  Vampires take half damage from cold, 
none from gas, and double from fire, although those with the Heat 
immunity take normal fire damage rather than double.  Other abilities:

* #REmbrace#n - Allows you to feed from the willing or defenceless.
* #ROrder#n - As if target lower generation vampire of your clan was charmed.
* #RVamptalk#n - A special vampire channel which distinguishes between clans.
* #RRegenerate#n - Vampires need to use this to regen, use: regen <number of rounds> 
* #RVclan#n - Shows information on the other members of a vampires clan.
* #RFeed#n - For feeding other vampires with your blood.
* #RPowers#n - Lists all the commands (NOT powers) available to you.
* #RClan -#n Shows your personal and clan disciplines. 
* #RDisciplines#n - shows all the disciplines that you know and their level.
* #RDefence/vampire#n - lowers and raises defences towards other vampires so they can feed
   from you/teach you disciplines. 
* #RTeach <target> <discipline>#n - teach other vampires disciplines. 
* #RUpkeep#n - shows what powers you are currently utilising. 
* #RFangs#n - Gives a free bite attack in combat. 
* #Rvarmor#n - Create vampire armor, cost 100 primal and 400 quest points.

Related Helps: Clandisc, Disciplines, and Class.
~

0 Clandisc~
Not all of these clans are available.

Assamite:    Celerity, Obfuscate, Quietus
Brujah:      Celerity, Potence, Presence
Setites:     Obfuscate, Presence, Serpentis	(Also Serpents of the Light)
Gangrel:     Animalism, Fortitude, Protean
Lasombra:    Dominate, Obtenebration, Potence
Malkavian:   Auspex, Dominate, Obfuscate
Nosferatu:   Animalism, Obfuscate, Potence
Ravnos:      Animalism, Chimerstry, Fortitude
Toreador:    Auspex, Celerity, Presence
Tremere:     Auspex, Dominate, Thaumaturgy
Tzimisce:    Animalism, Auspex, Vicissitude
Ventrue:     Dominate, Fortitude, Presence

Related Helps: Disciplines, Clans, and Vampires
~

0 Disciplines~
Each vampire has access to a number of disciplines, from which their powers 
stem.  Clan disciplines for each clan of vampires will max at 7, while non-clan
disciplines will max at 5.

There are eight basic disciplines to which all clans have access to:
* Animalism     - Control over Animals
* Auspex        - Extra sensory powers
* Celerity      - Great combat speed
* Dominate      - Hypnotic powers
* Fortitude     - Damage resistance
* Obfuscate     - Art of concealment
* Potence       - Supernatural strength
* Presence      - Charismatic aura's

There are also eight more clan-specific Disciplines which only a few clans can 
make use of:
* Chimerstry    - Illusionary powers
* Necromancy    - Mastery over the dead
* Obtenebration - Shadow magic
* Protean       - Shapeshifting
* Quietus       - Assassination powers
* Serpentis     - Wyrm abilities
* Thaumaturgy   - Blood magic
* Vicissitude   - Body control

Related Helps: Clandisc, 'help <discipline name>', and Vampire.
~

0 AUSPEX~
Auspex and Obfuscate tend to cancel out each others powers.
[*]       Heighten - Increases detection abilities.
[**]      Readaura - In depth analyzation of target(character or object).
[***]     Scry - Views a distant place.
[****]    Unveil - Views the thoughts of another person.
[******]  Omnipotence - Forms a spectral eye to continuously watch an area.
[*******] Mindblast - Injures the target through psychic assault.

Related Helps: Disciplines, and Vampire.
~

0 ANIMALISM~
[*]      Pigeon - Sends an object to target.
[**]     Beckon - Summons an animal.
[***]    Song - Stops the frenzy.
[****]   Beastwithin - Sends someone into a frenzy.
[*****]  Succulence - Increase the quality of a targets blood.
[******] Frenzy - Complete control over your own frenzy.
[*******] Fleshbond - take on some of the qualities of a bonded animal.

Related Helps: Disciplines, and Vampire.
~

0 CELERITY~
This Discipline explains the legendary superior quickness of vampires.  
They have the ability to move with amazing speed and become little more than a blur
to mortal eyes, obviously such an ability is extremely useful allowing the vampire to
hit and dodge faster than lesser opponents. Typing 'celerity renew' will renew your
celerity while you are still fighting.

Related Helps: Disciplines, and Vampire.
~

0 CHIMERSTRY~
[*]      Formillusion - Makes a mirror image of the target.
[**]     Phantasmal - Slashes with a chimerstral dagger.<auto>
[***]    Clone - Creates an clone of an object.
[****]   Falseappearance - Manipulates the form of an object.
[*****]  Control - Allows the user to control illusions.
